        "The objective of this project is to analyze the Zomato restaurant dataset and develop a machine learning regression model that can accurately predict a restaurant's aggregate rating based on its characteristics. The project involves cleaning and preprocessing the data, performing Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to identify important trends and relationships, engineering relevant features, and implementing multiple regression algorithms to estimate restaurant ratings. Model performance is evaluated using standard regression metrics such as Mean Absolute Error (MAE), Mean Squared Error (MSE), Root Mean Squared Error (RMSE), and R-squared (R²) score to identify the most accurate prediction model.\n",
